fields.name: Optimum Nutrition Hydro Whey Platinum 1.6kg
fields.description:
Platinum Hydrowhey is the fastest, purest, most advanced whey protein Optimum's ever developed. In a word: excellence. What else would you expect from the most proven protein brand?

By hydrolyzing the protein in this premium formula we've created our fastest-acting whey protein yet. Hydrolyzing breaks larger proteins down into smaller pieces that are able to get into your system rapidly, enabling your muscles to start rebuilding quickly. For added effectiveness, we've also enhanced this revolutionary formula with digestive enzymes and micronized branched chain amino acids (BCAAs). In addition to being fast, Platinum Hydrowhey is also ultra-pure. That's because it's made entirely with hydrolyzed whey protein isolates. So there's no excess fat, cholesterol, or lactose to slow down your progress.

Each serving is packed with a mighty 21g* of protein, nourishing with the everyday protein you need to fuel your body, sourced from high-quality ingredients.

fields.name: SO NUTRITION - Whey Isolate Zero 454g
fields.description:
Pure whey isolate contains a precise blend of proteins designed to create the 
optimal environment for exercise recovery and muscle growth. this protein blend 
contains fast digesting whey protein isolate and concentrate to fuel your muscles 
after hard and exhausting training. this refills your muscles with amino acids, the 
building blocks of its tissues.

Whey protein isolates are 90% pure protein by weight. they are the purest and most 
bioavailable form of whey protein that exists.

Whey protein is high in the essential branched-chain amino acids (bcaa’s) and very high 
in l-glutamine, the most abundant free amino acid in human blood. in addition whey 
protein contains essential amino acids (eaas). eaas are necessary for the human body 
and muscle tissues, but it cannot synthesize eaas so must be supplied by healthy diet.

fields.name: Whey Isolate 100 % - EnergyBody
fields.description:

Use: For one serving mix 30 g of powder (= 3 level measuring spoons) with 200 ml of water in a shaker for 20 seconds. Take 1-2 servings per day. The use after your training is especially recommended.
Important information: This product does not replace a varied and balanced diet and a healthy lifestyle.
Calcium contributes to a normal energy metabolism

fields.name: Pea Protein Isolate 1kg
fields.description:
Pea protein isolate is a plant protein with an excellent amino acid profile. It's made from premium-quality natural golden peas grown in Canada which have been dried and ground, then mixed with water to remove the fibre and starch components.

It's then ground and dried again to produce a product which is very high in protein, low in fat, easily digestible, and non-acidic. Low heat isolation is used to maximise bioavailability.

Pea protein is vegan and GMO free. It's also naturally free of dairy, gluten, soy, and other allergens*.

It mixes easily in a handshaker or blender, and also works well in recipes as it doesn't tend to dry out when baked like some other protein powders can. It can be used to make cookies, bars, pancakes, balls, muffins, and more.

fields.description:
It can be a challenge the first time you switch from a dairy whey to a plant-derived protein.
Vegan protein has a thicker texture, it's more floury than whey protein. It's a characteristic of plant-derived proteins.
So comparing a whey protein with a vegan protein can prove difficult.
For example, a soya steak is difficult to compare with a beef steak with regard to both its texture and flavour.
Our Vegan Protein is quickly absorbed by the body, making it perfect for use straight after training (up to 30 minutes).
You can also round off your diet by having a VEGAN PROTEIN shake for breakfast or before training.
Two-thirds of your protein intake should come through a varied and balanced diet.
